	;;   (or ... (or ...) ...) -> or of all, (or ... #f ...) toss the #f
	;; similarly for and
	;; (or ... (not (and ...))) -> (or ... (not x) [from here we know x is true] (not y)...)
	;; (or ... (not (and x1 x2 ...))) -> (or ... (not x1) (not x2)...), but is that simpler?
	
